<section class="legal-page" style="max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 6rem 2rem;">
  <div class="section-header" style="text-align: left; margin-bottom: 4rem;">
    <span class="section-tag">Legal</span>
    <h1 style="font-size: 3rem; margin-top: 1rem;">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p style="margin: 1.5rem 0 0;">Last updated: April 16, 2026</p>
  </div>

  <div class="docs-content" style="margin-left: 0; padding: 0; max-width: 100%;">
    <p>Your privacy is important to us. This policy explains how <strong><%= config.botName %></strong> handles your data when you use the bot or visit our website.</p>

    <h2>1. Data We Collect</h2>
    <p>We only collect data necessary for the functionality of our services:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>User IDs:</strong> To identify you and store your preferences (e.g., leveling, economy).</li>
      <li><strong>Server IDs:</strong> To store server-specific settings (e.g., prefix, moderation logs).</li>
      <li><strong>Message Content:</strong> Only processed in real-time for commands or moderation features; we do not store message history permanently unless specifically required by a feature (like modmail logs).</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. How We Use Data</h2>
    <p>Collected data is used solely to provide and improve the services offered by <%= config.botName %>. We do not sell or share your data with third parties.</p>

    <h2>3. Data Deletion</h2>
    <p>Users can request data deletion by contacting us via our support server. Additionally, when <%= config.botName %> leaves a server, we typically purge server-specific configuration after a grace period.</p>

    <h2>4. Security</h2>
    <p>We implement industry-standard security measures to protect your information, though no method of transmission over the internet is 100% secure.</p>

    <h2>5. Contact Us</h2>
    <p>If you have any questions about our privacy policy, please join our <a href="<%= config.supportServer %>">Support Server</a>.</p>
  </div>
</section>